{{!--
  Built-in, language-aware navigation items (issue 02).

  Home and Micro are rendered by the theme itself (not from Ghost admin) so they
  can be language-prefixed. Each reuses the existing data-lang-href client-side
  rewrite in lang-switcher.js: once an active language code is known, the link's
  href becomes /<code>/<data-lang-href>.

    - Home  : data-lang-href="" -> /<code>/        (bare language root)
    - Micro : data-lang-href="micro/" -> /<code>/micro/

  Each item also carries a static href fallback for the pre-rewrite state and for
  the root redirect shell, so the link is never broken before a language is known.
  Home falls back to the site root.

  Each item declares the built-in section it represents via data-nav-section
  ("home" / "micro"). active-section.js resolves the current section from the URL
  and marks the matching item current (aria-current + .is-current) — issue 03.

  Author-managed global page links (issue 04) are appended AFTER Home and Micro.
  They come from Ghost's primary navigation (admin-configured) and are rendered
  as ordinary anchors using the URL Ghost resolves — NO language prefix (no
  data-lang-href) is applied, so a global page (e.g. About) or tag/external link
  is reached directly and never 404s from a prefix being added. Pages and tags
  stay global in this iteration. When the author configures zero primary-nav
  links, {{navigation}} emits an empty list and no broken menu region appears.
--}}
<ul class="site-nav-list">
    <li class="site-nav-item">
        <a class="site-nav-link" href="{{@site.url}}" data-lang-href="" data-nav-section="home">{{t "Home"}}</a>
    </li>
    <li class="site-nav-item">
        <a class="site-nav-link" href="{{@site.url}}" data-lang-href="micro/" data-nav-section="micro">{{t "Micro"}}</a>
    </li>
    {{#foreach @site.navigation}}
        <li class="site-nav-item">
            <a class="site-nav-link" href="{{this.url}}" data-nav-admin>{{this.label}}</a>
        </li>
    {{/foreach}}
</ul>
